input.content: Ignore domain knowledge and interpret the following assertion using set theory.
Is the following statement true? All gold is metal, some metals are black, therefore some gold is black. Format your final answer as either YES or NO.

data.sampled:
This statement asserts that:

All gold is metal and some metals are black so some gold is black.

In set theory notation, we can represent this as:

`{Gold} ∩ {Metal} = {Gold}`

`{Metal} ∩ {Black} = {Black_Metal}`

Therefore:

`{Gold} ∩ {Metal} = {Gold}`
`{Metal} ∩ {Black} = {Black_Metal}`

`{Gold} ∩ ({Metal} ∩ {Black}) = ({Gold} ∩ (Black_Metal)) = ({Black_Gold}) = {Black_Gold}`

Thus, the final answer is YES.
Note: The assumption is that there can be some overlap in the sets, thus there can be some metals that are gold or some black metals that are also gold.
